IRS990.Desc: PREPARATION OF CHURCH AND COMMUNITY LEADERS THROUGH EDUCATION, COMMUNITY SERVICE, ATHLETICS, ARTS, AND STUDENT GOVERNMENT. DURING THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2018 506 STUDENTS ATTENDED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TUITION ASSISTANCE 1,207,850. LOSS ON DISPOSAL OF ASSETS -13,143.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: PART V, LINE 4 - INTENDED USES FOR ENDOWMENT FUNDS
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE TO REMAIN PERMANENTLY RESTRICTED. INCOME FROM ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE TO BE USED FOR TUITION ASSISTANCE, MERIT AWARDS AND OTHER THINGS AS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES.
ARCHBISHOP MURPHY HIGH SCHOOL PUBLICIZES ITS NONDISCRIMINATORY POLICY ON ITS ADMISSIONS AND FACT SHEETS AS WELL AS IN PRINT ADS.

PROCEDURES FOR MONITORING THE USE OF GRANT FUNDS THE SCHOOL ISSUES NO CASH GRANTS. RATHER IT OFFERS AID IN THE FORM OF REDUCED TUITION AND FEES TO ATTEND THE SCHOOL AND ITS PROGRAMS. STUDENTS MUST ATTEND THE SCHOOL TO OBTAIN ANY BENEFIT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: SCHEDULE K - PURPOSE OF ISSUE DESCRIPTION
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WA STATE HOUSING FINANCE COMMISSION DEBT USED FOR THE CONSTRUCTION AND EXPANSION OF SCHOOL FACILITIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DRAFT OF FORM 990 WILL BE REVIEWED BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES PRIOR TO FINALIZING THE RETURN AND FILING WITH THE IRS. A COPY OF RETURN WILL BE AVAILABLE TO THE ENTIRE BOARD OF TRUSTEES AT BOARD MEETING PRIOR TO FILING THE RETURN. A COPY OF THE FORM 990 IS MAINTAINED IN THE BUSINESS OFFICE FOR REVIEW BY ANY INTERESTED PARTIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS INCLUDED IN THE ORGANIZATIONS "POLICIES AND PROCEDURES" MANUAL. A COPY OF THE POLICY IS GIVEN TO EACH EMPLOYEE, BOARD MEMBER, AND VOLUNTEER AT THE BEGINNING OF THE TERM OF SERVICE OR EMPLOYMENT. EACH EMPLOYEE, BOARD MEMBER, AND VOLUNTEER IS REQUIRED TO SIGN AND DATE THE POLICY AT THE BEGINNING OF THEIR TERM OF SERVICE OR EMPLOYMENT AND EACH YEAR THEREAFTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OFFICER COMPENSATION IS REVIEWED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE SCHOOL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ARTICLES OF INCORPORATION, BY-LAWS, POLICIES AND PROCEDURES, THE CURRENT AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND THE CURRENT FEDERAL FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE IN THE BUSINESS OFFICE FOR ANY INTERESTED PARTIES.
